public class AccessTokenResponse
extends GenericData

OAuth 2.0 access token success response content as specified in Access Token Response.

Use AccessProtectedResource to authorize executed HTTP requests based on the accessToken, for example AccessProtectedResource.usingAuthorizationHeader(transport, response.accessToken).

1.0

scope

public String scope
(OPTIONAL) The scope of the access token as a list of space-delimited strings. The value of the "scope" parameter is defined by the authorization server. If the value contains multiple space-delimited strings, their order does not matter, and each string adds an additional access range to the requested scope.
